This paper is primarily focused on object detection in videos using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of general object tracking, which could potentially fall under robotics (cs.RO) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a temporal convolution network to incorporate temporal information, which could be considered as a form of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
